Seven people have been shot and killed in eMsahweni in Adams outside Durban. KZN Police spokesperson Jay Naicker provides more details. Courtesy #DStv403 KWAZULU-NATAL - KwaZulu-Natal police are investigating a mass murder at eMsahweni in Adams outside Durban. Seven men between the ages of 21 and 36, were allegedly shot dead execution-style. READ: Seven killed in KZN taxi crash Police spokesperson, Jay Naicker says it's still very early in the investigation and at this stage, it is too early to speculate the motive for the attack. He says investigations are continuing and community members are already coming forward with information. The motive for the shooting is unknown.